caption: Great place to eat they have amazing dishes Their meat is really nice and well cooked I really love that drunken noodles and fried rice  I normally prefer chicken and they cook it to perfection Their spicy sauce is also good A good place to hang out with friends as well  It's relatively cheap.

My son and his friends going to B.U. live on this food. We love it too, so much so that I came in, picked up the boy along with a large order of food and brought it all the way down to Wareham to share with my sister who was visiting from Nantucket!

Working a job site in Cambridge, I decided to order Noodle Street from GrubHub. The Spicy Miso Ramen is amazing and has some serious afterburner heat. They shipped the liquid portion in a separate container, so the large fried tofu chunks were still crispy, and the other ingredients seemed fresh. The steamed gyozos (side order) are soft and sweet. I'll definitely order from here again.

This is doubtless one of the most attractive place in the region. Whenever I visit this place I am highly happy. They keep their very high  level service and the highest level of cooking  they offer. You no doubt will love this place. Warmly  recommended.
This place is great! Affordable rates, large portions and the staff are consistently welcoming.
Visited this place after 11 years and the taste hasn't changed at all... You can never go wrong with Drunken Noodles at Noodle St.
I visit this spot a lot since I work close by. I like how their service is always fantastic and they keep the spot clean consistently. Rates are affordable and they serve generous portions.
I absolutely enjoy the food and service, excellent location next to my apartment. The employees are always helpful. Will come visit again.

best restaurant in Boston. The manager there is awesome and it is reasonable on price as well. Try the drunken noodles, you will thank me :)

I ended up eating my fried chicken and leaving as I didn't want to argue with him. 0/5 for customer service.

Noodle street offered me a really bad service. I ordered a noodle and what I got is totally different from what they appears on the menu. On the menu, they literally wrote that the noodle comes with the boiled egg, roasted chicken, and with vegetables, as what also appears on the picture of the noodle. When I got my noodle, only pale noodles with a few white low-quality chicken. I asked the waiter, waiter told me what appears on the picture is not what I should get. Are you kidding me!? and then I asked his boss. The boss was extremely impolite and said the same thing with the waiter. Really think twice before you go into that restaurant.

I really honestly just love this place and can't get enough of it.  When I was a BU student this was a regular dinner spot, lunch takeout, quick thai iced tea to go, family from out of town, you name it, its the place to go.  We still make the pilgrimage from Medford every now and again.  The tom yum noodle soup and the pad thai are my two favs, and of course the thai iced tea.  Great crab rangoons.  Never actually eaten anything bad here at all.
